<subSubSection id="8DF971D4FFED392A1A82FDF7FCBAFCC8" pageId="10" pageNumber="455" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C55C225FFFED392A1A82FDF7FE98FD3C" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFED392A1A82FDF7FEB7FDA9" bold="true" box="[199,332,546,572]" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">Discussion.</emphasis>
The male described herein exhibits common features with females, such as distal flagellomeres greatly elongated, palpal segment 3 with sensory pit at 2/3 of its length, wing membrane slightly infuscated with minute microtrichia, veins brown, cell r 
<subScript id="5967201AFFED392A1817FDA8FDA1FD1E" attach="left" box="[594,602,637,651]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">3</subScript>
with intercalary vein, r-m crossvein slightly shorter than petiole of M, and halter pale brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C55C225FFFED392A1A82FD66FCBAFCC8" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="02E359DCFFED392A1B74FD66FE29FD58" authorityName="Spinelli &amp; Grogan" authorityYear="1984" box="[305,466,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Macrurohelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="455" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monotheca">
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFED392A1B74FD66FEB3FD59" box="[305,328,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFED392A1B12FD66FE29FD58" box="[343,466,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">monotheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to males of 
<taxonomicName id="02E359DCFFED392A1899FD66FCA0FD59" authorityName="Spinelli &amp; Grogan" authorityYear="1999" box="[732,859,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Macrurohelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="455" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yamana">
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFED392A1899FD66FD08FD59" box="[732,755,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFED392A1947FD66FCA0FD59" box="[770,859,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">yamana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="02E359DCFFED392A19D4FD66FBF6FD58" authority="Spinelli &amp; Ronderos &amp; Grogan, 2022" authorityName="Spinelli &amp; Ronderos &amp; Grogan" authorityYear="2022" box="[913,1037,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Macrurohelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="455" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="donatoi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFED392A19D4FD66FC53FD59" box="[913,936,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFED392A19F2FD66FBF6FD58" box="[951,1037,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">donatoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFED392A1E51FD66FBA8FD58" bold="true" box="[1044,1107,691,717]" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ECA44336FFED392A1E51FD66FBA8FD58" box="[1044,1107,691,717]" pageId="10" pageNumber="455" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
However, 
<taxonomicName id="02E359DCFFED392A1E8BFD66FAB6FD59" authorityName="Spinelli &amp; Grogan" authorityYear="1999" box="[1230,1357,691,716]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Macrurohelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="455" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yamana">
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFED392A1E8BFD66FAB6FD59" box="[1230,1357,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">M. yamana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the shallow, narrow posteromedian excavation of sternite 9, the gonocoxite is as long as the gonostylus, and the parameres are fractured at mid-length. Males of 
<taxonomicName id="02E359DCFFED392A18FDFD2EFCCFFC80" authorityName="Spinelli &amp; Ronderos &amp; Grogan" authorityYear="2022" box="[696,820,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Macrurohelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="455" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="donatoi">
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFED392A18FDFD2EFD34FC81" box="[696,719,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFED392A189BFD2EFCCFFC80" box="[734,820,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">donatoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="02E359DCFFED392A198CFD2EFB91FC80" authorityName="Spinelli &amp; Grogan" authorityYear="1984" box="[969,1130,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Macrurohelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="455" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monotheca">
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFED392A198CFD2EFC1BFC81" box="[969,992,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFED392A19AAFD2EFB91FC80" box="[1007,1130,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="455">monotheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the apicolateral process of tergite 9 bearing a short inner peg, the posteromedian excavation of sternite 9 is narrow and shallow, and by the aedeagus with convex lateral margins and slender basal arms
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
